A MAG is denoted as 𝒢 = ( 𝒱 , ℰ , { 𝐗 ( m ) } m ∈ ℳ ) \mathcal{G}=(\mathcal{V},\mathcal{E},\{\mathbf{X}^{(m)}\}_{m\in\mathcal{M}}) ,
where 𝒱 \mathcal{V} is the set of nodes with N = | 𝒱 | N=|\mathcal{V}| , ℰ \mathcal{E} is the set of edges, and ℳ \mathcal{M} indexes the available modalities (e.g., text and images).
For each node v i v_{i} under modality m m , we associate a modality-specific feature vector 𝐱 i ( m ) ∈ ℝ d m \mathbf{x}_{i}^{(m)}\in\mathbb{R}^{d_{m}} , obtained by encoding the raw modality data with a pre-trained modality encoder (e.g., Sentence-BERT (Reimers and Gurevych, 2019 ) and T5 (Raffel et al. , 2020 ) for text; ViT (Wu et al. , 2020a ) and DINOv2 (Oquab et al. , 2023 ) for images).
For each modality m m , the embeddings of all nodes are organized into a feature matrix 𝐗 ( m ) ∈ ℝ N × d m \mathbf{X}^{(m)}\in\mathbb{R}^{N\times d_{m}} .
All modalities share a common relational structure represented by the adjacency matrix 𝐀 ∈ ℝ N × N \mathbf{A}\in\mathbb{R}^{N\times N} , with the corresponding degree matrix 𝐃 \mathbf{D} , where 𝐃 i ​ i = ∑ j 𝐀 i ​ j \mathbf{D}_{ii}=\sum_{j}\mathbf{A}_{ij} and 𝐃 i ​ j = 0 \mathbf{D}_{ij}=0 for i ≠ j i\neq j . To capture structural smoothness, the symmetrically normalized adjacency matrix and Laplacian of 𝒢 \mathcal{G} are represented by 𝐀 ~ = 𝐃 − 1 / 2 ​ 𝐀𝐃 − 1 / 2 \tilde{\mathbf{A}}=\mathbf{D}^{-1/2}\mathbf{A}\mathbf{D}^{-1/2} and 𝐋 = 𝐈 − 𝐀 ~ \mathbf{L}=\mathbf{I}-\tilde{\mathbf{A}} , respectively.

In this paper, we consider three Graph-centric Tasks , including (1) Node Classification : assigning category labels to unlabeled nodes;
(2) Link Prediction : estimating whether an edge ( u , v ) (u,v) should exist in ℰ \mathcal{E} ; (3) Node Clustering : grouping nodes into clusters by applying standard clustering algorithms to the learned node embeddings; and three Modality-centric Tasks , including (1) Modality Retrieval : given a query from one modality (e.g., text), retrieving its corresponding representation in another modality;
(2) Graph-to-Text Generation (G2Text) : producing textual outputs conditioned on a target node along with task instructions and its graph neighborhood;
(3) Graph-to-Image Generation (G2Image) : synthesizing images using diffusion models conditioned on the node’s textual descriptions and the associated graph context. Further discussion of these tasks is presented in Appendix D .
